      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As Shakespeare once said, “what’s in a name?” Sure, you can nitpick about whether or not the Ford Mustang is a real sports car based on definitions you and others adhere to, but ultimately the Blue Oval and others are going to keep regarding the pony car as a sports car, just like how some consider it a muscle car when back in the day it wasn’t viewed as such a thing. Rather than play semantics games, we’re happy to let the Mustang take the W and ride on.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
